OL,3,CWelsh Conservatives offer home tax
OL,4,Cdeal to back Labour budget
OL,6,FDarren Millar, leader of the Welsh
OL,7,FConservatives, has written to Baroness
OL,8,FMorgan, offering to discuss a budget
OL,9,Fagreement if the Welsh Government
OL,10,Fconsiders scrapping the land
OL,11,Ftransaction tax, the Welsh equivalent
OL,12,Fof stamp duty.
OL,14,FWhile Labour is the largest party in
OL,15,Fthe Senedd, it does not have a
OL,16,Fmajority.
OL,18,FWhen passing its last budget in March,
OL,19,Fthe Welsh Government needed the help
OL,20,Fof an opposition member to get it
OL,21,Fthrough by a tight margin.
